<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Chelsea have rejected offers from Inter Milan for N'Golo Kante involving Christian Eriksen and Marcelo Brozovic.</p>

<p>Chelsea would rather sell Jorginho ahead of Kante and have no interest in Eriksen or Brozovic.</p>

<p>Antonio Conte has been eyeing up a move to reunite with Kante, who he brought to Stamford Bridge from Leicester four years ago.</p>

<p>Chelsea have rejected an approach from Inter Milan for their midfielder N'Golo Kante</p>

<p>Eriksen, who only joined Inter from Tottenham in the January transfer window, has been in and out of the side under Conte. </p>

<p>Jorginho has struggled to make himself a prominent part of Frank Lampard's future plans at Chelsea.</p>

<p>The Italian midfielder followed former boss Maurizio Sarri to Chelsea from Napoli in the summer of 2018. </p>

<p>Earlier on Thursday Michy Batshuayi completed his move to Crystal Palace on loan. </p>

<p>Inter Milan's approach for Kante included a swap deal with former Spurs star Christian Eriksen</p>
